  "prompt": "What I have to do after I catch pokemon in pokemon go?",
  "response": "After catching a Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO, you have several options:\n\n1. Transfer the Pok\u00e9mon\n- Transfer duplicate Pok\u00e9mon to the Professor\n- Receive candy for that Pok\u00e9mon species\n- Free up storage space\n\n2. Power up the Pok\u00e9mon\n- Increase its Combat Power (CP)\n- Make it stronger for battles\n- Requires Stardust and Candy\n\n3. Evolve the Pok\u00e9mon\n- Transform into a new form\n- Requires specific amount of candy\n- Can improve Pok\u00e9mon's stats\n\n4. Add to your Pok\u00e9dex\n- Record the catch in your collection\n- Track your progress in catching different species\n\n5. Use in Battles\n- Fight in Gyms\n- Participate in Raid Battles\n- Team Rocket encounters\n\n6. Keep for Collection\n- Some players collect rare or high-CP Pok\u00e9mon\n- Save unique or special Pok\u00e9mon\n\n7. Use in Trades\n- Trade with other players\n- Potentially get special or regional Pok\u00e9mon\n\n8. Check its Individual Values (IVs)\n- Assess the Pok\u00e9mon's potential\n- Determine its overall quality\n\nChoose the action that best suits your gameplay strategy and goals.",
